description.plain:
Tyshon Dwayne Nobles (b. October 27, 1990), better known by his stage name T-Wayne (also known as Rickey), is a Houston, Texas native who came to fame when his song “Nasty Freestyle” blew up on Vine. He is currently signed to 300 Entertainment and affiliated with Brick Squad Monopoly.

He’s released two mixtapes: Who is Rickey Wayne? and Who is Rickey Wayne 2.

songs.title: Nasty Freestyle

description.plain:
This song is a freestyle over Bandit Gang Marco’s “Nasty.”

The song gained a lot of attention over Vine, with parody videos featuring the first two lines becoming a staple of the social media app. Largely because of streaming, “Nasty Freestyle” eventually went Top 10 in the US, with the original also benefiting.

songs.title: Fuck Russ

description.plain: This song actually isn’t about the musician Russ, it is about one of T-Wayne’s and producer Cam Taylor’s old collaborators Russel Smith. In the song T-Wayne is talking about how Russel is an enemy and he flexes on him with his diamonds, cars, etc. T-Wayne also put a video on his Instagram explaining this.
